OL,3,CNottingham attacks killer should have
OL,4,Csentence changed, court hears
OL,6,FThe sentencing judge, Mr Justice
OL,7,FTurner, told Calocane his "sickening
OL,8,Fcrimes" meant he would likely be
OL,9,Fdetained indefinitely in a high-
OL,10,Fsecurity hospital "very probably for
OL,11,Fthe rest of your life".
OL,13,FHe also ruled Calocane should be
OL,14,Fsubject to further restrictions if
OL,15,Fever discharged from hospital, which
OL,16,Fwould need to be approved by the
OL,17,FJustice Secretary or a Mental Health
OL,18,FTribunal.
