OL,3,CNottingham attacks killer should have
OL,4,Csentence changed, court hears
OL,6,FAttorney General Victoria Prentis
OL,7,Freferred the sentence to the Court of
OL,8,FAppeal in February, with lawyers
OL,9,Ftelling a hearing on Wednesday (8 May)
OL,10,Fthat it was "unduly lenient".
OL,12,FSpeaking at the hearing, Deanna Heer
OL,13,FKC, representing the Attorney
OL,14,FGeneral's Office (AGO), said Calocane
OL,15,Fshould instead be given a life
OL,16,Fsentence as part of a "hybrid" order,
OL,17,Fwhere he would be treated in hospital
OL,18,Fbefore serving the remainder of his
OL,19,Fsentence in prison.
