OL,3,CNottingham attacks killer should have
OL,4,Csentence changed, court hears
OL,6,F"We trusted in our system, foolishly
OL,7,Fas it turns out. We do not dispute
OL,8,Fthat the murderer is mentally unwell
OL,9,Fand has been for a number of years.
OL,11,F"However the pre-mediated planning,
OL,12,Fthe collection of lethal weapons,
OL,13,Fhiding in the shadows and brutality of
OL,14,Fthe attacks are that of an individual
OL,15,Fwho knew exactly what he was doing. He
OL,16,Fknew entirely that it was wrong but he
OL,17,Fdid it anyway."
OL,19,F"He understood the nature of his
OL,20,Fconduct"
