OL,3,CNottingham attacks killer should have
OL,4,Csentence changed, court hears
OL,6,FIn written submissions to the Court of
OL,7,FAppeal hearing, the AGO said: "The
OL,8,Flearned judge failed to give
OL,9,Fsufficient weight to the evidence that
OL,10,Fthe offender's culpability was not
OL,11,Fextinguished.
OL,13,F"Whilst it is accepted that his
OL,14,Fability to exercise self-control and
OL,15,Fform a rational judgment was
OL,16,Fsubstantially impaired, he understood
OL,17,Fthe nature of his conduct and that it
OL,18,Fwas wrong, even in the context of his
OL,19,Fpsychotic beliefs.
