OL,3,CNottingham attacks killer should have
OL,4,Csentence changed, court hears
OL,6,F"Having identified that the offender's
OL,7,Fculpability was low, the learned judge
OL,8,Ffailed to consider the aggravating
OL,9,Ffeatures which required an uplift from
OL,10,Fthe starting point for a single
OL,11,Foffence.
OL,13,F"As a result, although the learned
OL,14,Fjudge made a significant uplift to
OL,15,Freflect totality, the custodial term
OL,16,Ffailed adequately to reflect the
OL,17,Fseriousness of the offending."
